1
00:00:46,159 --> 00:00:46,719
Uncle Xiang.

2
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,640
Nice flowers.

3
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:53,799
Business is good, huh?

4
00:00:54,119 --> 00:00:54,920
Sorry,

5
00:00:54,920 --> 00:00:56,119
we're closed for today.

6
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:57,399
What?

7
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,359
I walk in and you shut up shop?

8
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:01,799
That's how unwelcome I am?

9
00:01:06,239 --> 00:01:07,640
This transfer agreement,

10
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:08,799
I've already checked it over for you.

11
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:10,280
Just sign it.

12
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:11,560
Saves everyone the trouble.

13
00:01:13,959 --> 00:01:15,719
I've run this flower shop my whole life.

14
00:01:16,359 --> 00:01:17,799
I eat and sleep right here.

15
00:01:18,519 --> 00:01:20,840
Where am I supposed to go now?

16
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,920
The whole of Portland Street now

17
00:01:25,719 --> 00:01:27,519
belongs to the United Righteous Group.

18
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:29,599
You're the last holdout who won't budge.

19
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:30,640
You got a death wish?

20
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:31,400
No, I don't.

21
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:32,560
Keep this up and I'll call the cops.

22
00:01:32,719 --> 00:01:33,799
Go ahead, call them.

23
00:01:34,799 --> 00:01:37,000
We've been nice and civil with you,

24
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:40,239
but you just don't know what's good for you.

25
00:01:40,879 --> 00:01:41,200
Grab him!

26
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:43,840
No, don't!

27
00:01:45,239 --> 00:01:46,480
Today, this agreement,

28
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:48,000
you're signing it whether you like it or not.

29
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:49,079
No, please!

30
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:56,319
And who the hell are you?

31
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,480
A hero coming to save the flower shop?

32
00:02:01,799 --> 00:02:03,040
Uncle Xiang has run this shop here

33
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,200
for over 20 years.

34
00:02:04,239 --> 00:02:05,400
What gives you the right to kick him out?

35
00:02:08,159 --> 00:02:09,159
What's it to you?

36
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:10,000
Playing the hero?

37
00:02:12,039 --> 00:02:12,919
Acting all righteous?

38
00:02:15,439 --> 00:02:15,960
Still staring?

39
00:02:17,719 --> 00:02:18,120
I dare you to keep staring.

40
00:02:52,479 --> 00:02:53,400
What the hell?

41
00:02:54,199 --> 00:02:55,120
Ah Fei, you little bitch!

42
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,520
Making trouble on my turf?

43
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:00,319
What are you doing?

44
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:04,520
Hello, Big Sister.

45
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,039
Now get lost!

46
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:11,840
Dad!

47
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,080
Dad!

48
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,639
They didn't hurt you, did they?

49
00:03:14,639 --> 00:03:15,439
I'm fine, I'm fine.

50
00:03:15,599 --> 00:03:16,639
They came to shake down the shop again.

51
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:17,960
Ah Qiang saved us.

52
00:03:24,479 --> 00:03:25,319
Ah Qiang.

53
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:31,000
Weren't you such a big shot before?

54
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,800
And now look at you.

55
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:35,120
Trampled on and you don't even fight back.

56
00:03:36,639 --> 00:03:38,319
Aren't you the big shot now, Big Sister.

57
00:03:39,039 --> 00:03:40,919
Don't take that tone with me.

58
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,360
A few years in prison,

59
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:45,199
and you've lost all your fight?

60
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,439
You're like a dead man now.

61
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,960
You didn't used to be like this.

62
00:03:53,599 --> 00:03:54,800
You didn't used to be like this either.

63
00:03:57,639 --> 00:03:58,599
Liang Zhiqiang.

64
00:04:00,439 --> 00:04:00,919
You don't know what I

65
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:01,840
went through all these years.

66
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:02,960
I don't know,

67
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:05,280
and I don't want to know.

68
00:04:05,919 --> 00:04:06,879
All I know now

69
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:07,719
is that Ah Hong treats you well.

70
00:04:07,719 --> 00:04:08,879
He takes good care of you.

71
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:10,759
The past

72
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:12,560
is best left alone.

73
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,279
Honey,

74
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,240
you're home so early.

75
00:04:37,639 --> 00:04:38,879
I missed you so much.

76
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,399
What are you doing?

77
00:04:46,399 --> 00:04:47,519
Help me, Brother Hong!

78
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:09,519
Xie Guanhong!

79
00:05:11,279 --> 00:05:13,199
I don't care if you mess around with women outside,

80
00:05:14,639 --> 00:05:15,920
but you brought her home?

81
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,360
You disgust me.

82
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:21,480
Laughing?

83
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,399
Your brother got out of prison,

84
00:05:24,399 --> 00:05:25,680
and he doesn't even have a decent job.

85
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,480
Couldn't you have helped him out?

86
00:05:27,639 --> 00:05:28,759
Some brother you are.

87
00:05:28,759 --> 00:05:29,720
What's so funny?

88
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:35,319
Whether my brother has a job,

89
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:37,199
you know better than I do, don't you?

90
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,759
What?

91
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,879
Seeing your old flame,

92
00:05:44,639 --> 00:05:45,480
feeling sorry for him?

93
00:05:47,079 --> 00:05:47,920
Having regrets?

94
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:50,560
That's nonsense.

95
00:05:53,399 --> 00:05:54,639
I didn't even say anything.

96
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:55,959
So why so defensive?

97
00:05:56,639 --> 00:05:57,800
How melodramatic.

98
00:06:01,079 --> 00:06:01,920
Sister Ah Jiao,

99
00:06:02,639 --> 00:06:03,480
These days,

100
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,720
sob stories are so out of fashion.

101
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:08,480
It's been 20 years and you still haven't forgotten.

102
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:11,319
Now that's true devotion.

103
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,199
Or is it that

104
00:06:14,639 --> 00:06:16,680
Sister Ah Jiao wants them both?

105
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:17,560
Shut your mouth!

106
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:18,519
What?

107
00:06:18,759 --> 00:06:19,600
Did I say something wrong?

108
00:06:20,279 --> 00:06:22,519
Brother Hong, look at Big Sister.

109
00:06:24,879 --> 00:06:26,319
For the sake of your brother,

110
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:28,399
she's even crying.

111
00:06:29,079 --> 00:06:30,319
And this brother of yours,

112
00:06:30,319 --> 00:06:32,040
what's really going on in his head?

113
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,759
Who could ever know?

114
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,120
Matters between brothers,

115
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,199
matters of this family,

116
00:06:43,879 --> 00:06:45,120
it's not your place to butt in.

117
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:58,959
Brothers,

118
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,920
It's time to show Camel

119
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:04,680
just what we're made of.

120
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,920
Once we take out Camel,

121
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,079
I, Cannon,

122
00:07:12,079 --> 00:07:14,319
will be the boss of the United Righteous Group.

123
00:07:14,439 --> 00:07:17,759
And then the whole world will be ours.

124
00:07:17,879 --> 00:07:21,040
Brothers, we'll live like kings.

125
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:26,040
Boss!

126
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:26,879
Move out!

127
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:30,920
Let's go!

128
00:07:32,439 --> 00:07:34,759
All right, hurry up and pack it all up.

129
00:07:35,279 --> 00:07:37,120
Today we hack him to death!

130
00:07:37,519 --> 00:07:38,639
Hack him to death!

131
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:43,680
Uncle Cannon!

132
00:07:45,199 --> 00:07:45,720
Uncle Cannon!

133
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,120
What's going on? Quite the operation.

134
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:48,279
What are you doing here?

135
00:07:48,279 --> 00:07:49,839
Go home and mind your own business.

136
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:50,839
Uncle Cannon,

137
00:07:52,199 --> 00:07:53,040
Take me to see it.

138
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:54,000
Just one look.

139
00:07:54,399 --> 00:07:55,240
Let me see some action.

140
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,439
See what?

141
00:07:56,959 --> 00:07:58,920
If your mom finds out, she'll kill me.

142
00:07:59,879 --> 00:08:01,120
Uncle Cannon,

143
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:03,560
My dad won't take me, and neither will you.

144
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,319
Of all my uncles, you love me the most.

145
00:08:05,319 --> 00:08:06,959
Please, Uncle Cannon, please.

146
00:08:08,839 --> 00:08:09,639
Look me in the eyes.

147
00:08:09,639 --> 00:08:10,000
Fine.

148
00:08:11,439 --> 00:08:12,279
I really can't take you.

149
00:08:15,199 --> 00:08:15,680
Brother Wen,

150
00:08:15,879 --> 00:08:17,120
Come on, take me to see it.

151
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,759
I'll run errands, watch the bags, anything.

152
00:08:19,639 --> 00:08:21,240
You think this is some martial arts flick?

153
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:22,439
Stop causing trouble.

154
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,319
Brother Wen,

155
00:08:25,079 --> 00:08:26,680
Just one look, just one look.

156
00:08:27,319 --> 00:08:28,120
I'll just watch from the side.

157
00:08:31,639 --> 00:08:32,120
Brother Qiang,

158
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,120
I'll leave this little pest to you.

159
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,320
Brother Cannon and I have some business to handle.

160
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,159
That's it for now.

161
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:38,000
Who are you calling a pest?

162
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:39,799
Working that hard, huh?

163
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,879
Forget it, nobody wants to take you.

164
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:45,559
Hold on.

165
00:08:47,279 --> 00:08:48,120
I recognize you.

166
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:48,919
It was you that night

167
00:08:48,919 --> 00:08:50,440
who brought my drunk old man home.

168
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:53,039
I even heard him mention it. He said

169
00:08:53,159 --> 00:08:54,399
you were his best brother.

170
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:13,759
Brother Cannon,

171
00:09:14,879 --> 00:09:16,399
You've actually got the nerve to show up.

172
00:09:17,879 --> 00:09:20,519
Today, you're not walking out of here alive.

173
00:09:40,799 --> 00:09:41,799
I heard a little rumor today.

174
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:43,559
You used to chase my mom back in the day.

175
00:09:43,679 --> 00:09:45,519
You were just a piece in their game to play.

176
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:47,759
Sick rhyme, right?

177
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,679
What kind of nonsense is that?

178
00:09:49,399 --> 00:09:49,879
Would your dad ever beat you?

179
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,559
Xie Guanhong, I mean.

180
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:53,320
No way he would.

181
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,159
All he does is sit in his office

182
00:09:55,159 --> 00:09:56,200
and make a few phone calls.

183
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:58,200
Brother Qiang.

184
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,200
I heard you were a real badass back then.

185
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,120
Show me the ropes.

186
00:10:00,399 --> 00:10:01,240
Show you how to haul goods, you mean.

187
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:03,799
Don't you look down on me.

188
00:10:04,279 --> 00:10:05,000
Let me tell you,

189
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,240
if it ever came to a fight,

190
00:10:06,759 --> 00:10:08,600
I'd win for sure. I'm tough, all right?

191
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:13,720
Brother Qiang.

192
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:14,480
No, wait.

193
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:15,960
Master Qiang.

194
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,279
Lord Qiang.

195
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:18,440
Just teach me one move.

196
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:19,480
Just one move, okay?

197
00:10:19,919 --> 00:10:20,720
No moves for you.

198
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,279
Get back here!

199
00:10:48,639 --> 00:10:49,840
Fine!

200
00:10:50,559 --> 00:10:52,200
That coward Xie Guanhong,

201
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,039
doesn't dare face me himself,

202
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,759
so he sends his own son.

203
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,720
Xie Guanhong, that spineless coward.

204
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:20,399
And his son's

205
00:11:20,399 --> 00:11:22,559
just as gutless, always running away.

206
00:11:24,399 --> 00:11:24,840
Today,

207
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:28,840
I'll beat you to a bloody pulp.

208
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,039
Don't kill me!

209
00:11:44,960 --> 00:11:46,519
Liang Zhiqiang.

210
00:11:50,759 --> 00:11:51,720
What a rare visitor.

211
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:55,720
You say you're done with the underworld,

212
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,039
but that's all a lie.

213
00:11:58,799 --> 00:12:00,399
I'm not here for the underworld.

214
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,000
I'm here for this kid.

215
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:07,279
Get him!

216
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:31,240
Go!

217
00:12:42,519 --> 00:12:43,120
Officer Chen,

218
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,200
The abandoned factory outside the city,

219
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:46,639
there's a gang fight going on.

220
00:12:47,159 --> 00:12:48,000
Get over here fast!

221
00:12:53,759 --> 00:12:54,519
Ah Qiang,

222
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:56,240
let's talk.

223
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,519
I took your call and brought my men right over.

224
00:13:00,159 --> 00:13:01,240
Good thing nobody got killed.

225
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:03,240
Right.

226
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,519
And the Dongxing gang?

227
00:13:05,519 --> 00:13:06,559
We did nab quite a few of them.

228
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,720
But on the United Righteous side,

229
00:13:09,799 --> 00:13:11,200
most of them slipped away clean.

230
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:13,919
Let me ask you something.

231
00:13:14,639 --> 00:13:15,320
Are you planning to go back?

232
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,519
I only went there to save someone.

233
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,399
I'm not going back to the gang.

234
00:13:19,039 --> 00:13:19,919
You don't want to go back.

235
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:22,200
My advice is to stay away from Xie Guanhong,

236
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,200
Zheng Baojiao,

237
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:24,639
and even Xie Zihao.

238
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:25,960
You don't want to go back,

239
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:26,919
but they want you to go back.

240
00:13:31,039 --> 00:13:32,200
Or you go back,

241
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:33,360
and become my informant.
